{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6b2375a3-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s420"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"420"},"text":"§ 420.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Piers and cribs on Mississippi and St. Croix Rivers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The owners of sawmills on the Mississippi River and the Saint Croix River in the States of Wisconsin and Minnesota are authorized and empowered under the direction of the Secretary of the Army, to construct piers or cribs in front of their mill property on the banks of the river, for the protection of their mills and rafts against damage by floods and ice: ","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided, however","children":[],"tail":", That the piers or cribs so constructed shall not interfere with or obstruct the navigation of the river. And in case any pier or crib constructed under authority of this section shall at any time, and for any cause, be found to obstruct the navigation of the river, the Government expressly reserves the right to remove or direct the removal of it, at the cost and expense of the owners thereof."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6b2375a4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(R.S. § 5254; ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1882-05-01/ch112"},"text":"May 1, 1882, ch. 112","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/22/52"},"text":"22 Stat. 52","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343"},"text":"July 26, 1947, ch. 343","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 205(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6b25bf95-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6b25bf96-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id6b25bf97-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"R.S. § 5254 derived from ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1873-03-03/ch278"},"text":"act Mar. 3, 1873, ch. 278","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/17/606"},"text":"17 Stat. 606","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id6b25bf98-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1882—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1882-05-01"},"text":"May 1, 1882","children":[],"tail":", inserted reference to Saint Croix River in the States of Wisconsin and Minnesota."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id6b25bf99-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id6b25bf9a-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Department of War designated Department of the Army and title of Secretary of War changed to Secretary of the Army by section 205(a) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343/tII"},"text":"act July 26, 1947, ch. 343, title II","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":". Section 205(a) of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1947","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by section 53 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/641"},"text":"70A Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":". Section 1 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956","children":[],"tail":", enacted “Title 10, Armed Forces” which in sections 3010 to 3013 continued Department of the Army under administrative supervision of Secretary of the Army."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id6b25bf9b-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions, powers, and duties of Secretary of the Army and other offices and officers of Department of the Army under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s401"},"text":"section 401 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to extent that they relate generally to location and clearances of bridges and causeways in navigable waters of United States transferred to and vested in Secretary of Transportation by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/670/s6/g/6/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–670, § 6(g)(6)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/941"},"text":"80 Stat. 941","children":[],"tail":", which created Department of Transportation. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/449"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–449","children":[],"tail":" amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s401"},"text":"section 401 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to reflect transfer made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/670/s6/g/6/A"},"text":"section 6(g)(6)(A) of Pub. L. 89–670","children":[],"tail":", and repealed section 6(g)(6)(A)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
